The paper deals with the problem of deadlock prevention in computer systems, which is a fundamental issue in operating systems (cs.OS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses priority digraphs, which are a type of directed graph used in graph theory and computer science to model dependencies and relationships between tasks or processes. This makes the paper relevant to the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), systems and control (cs.SY), and programming languages (cs.PL).
